        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Heh, Necros own in duels and pvp if they use their strengths.</P><P>run to max range drop splurt and IB, possibly BoD to counter the chants he's going to put on you, then chain Drain Soul till he dies. </P><P>Shadow Step to keep out of his melee range.<BR> <BR>If you have a circlet of shadow to break targetting, he's doomed. He wont have his see invis song up either, most likely. It will be much easier once you get deflux.</P><P>Don't use a pet, he will simply charm it or fear it off.</P><P><BR>In the Bazaar arena I had just finished killing 2 guildies and was Demiliching up when I was jumped at 2 bubs by a level 60 BOTS warrior with a big axe.  I made him run from the arena at a sliver of life, I was by then fh. ;)</P><P>Melees are cake.</P><P><BR>Old School Necro,KOS since the dawn of time!<br><BR><img src="http://thegeekhost.com/gravedirt/atari1a.jpg" border=0><img src="http://thegeekhost.com/gravedirt/atari2a.jpg" border=0><br><BR>Iksar Defiler of the 57th shedding <br><BR>Frayed Knot - The Rathe<br><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
